lead_paragraph: World number one Novak Djokovic produced sublime form to clinch an unprecedented fifth men's title at Indian Wells with a 6-2 6-0 demolition of big-serving Canadian Milos Raonic in the men's final on Sunday.

headline.main: Djokovic Crushes Raonic, Wins Fifth Indian Wells Title
